review_blob: Beautiful amber with a large, slightly off-white long lasting head that leaves lots of lacing. Medium body, lively carbonation. This beer is better than average because of its finish which is spicy, fruity, slightly sweet but wonderfully balanced.

Pours almost black with an average tan head. Very smooth on the palate with medium body. Tastes of caramel and dark chocolate. A little sweet. I knew little of Lift Bridge before trying this bottle and I was very favorably impressed.

I dont think of myself as a hop head but I really enjoyed this, maybe because it is balanced with a good deal of maltiness. As noted elsewhere, pours copper colored with a good head that lasts well. Drinks smooth on the palate with strong spruce notes and a remarkably pleasant bitterness. Well done Surly.

Pours cloudy yellow with a very big white long lasting head. Aroma of grass and orange peel. Medium body very pleasant on the tongue. Flavors of spice and fruit including clove and citrus. A very good beer.
Pours reddish brown with a creamy medium lasting head. Strong aroma of caramel malt. Slightly fizzy carbonation with medium body. Very interesting taste of brown sugar although not too sweet.

Smoky sweetness that I found delicious. Interestingly I didnt notice the smoke so much in the aroma, more just the malt but on drinking I found it strong enough to strongly balance the underlying sweetness. Pours very dark red black with a big brown head which quickly dissipates. I found it to have good body with fairly soft carbonation (softer than I expected . The taste, as said was smoky sweet; I would describe the later as bubble gum rather than the banana I expected. Fades to slightly boozy. I enjoyed this enormously. It certainly is one of Surlys most interesting brews.
Poors black with little head which dissipates quickly. Sweet as expected, malty with some coffee. Creamy on the palate with a little fizziness. Very easy to drink
Several folks here have mentioned "tart but not sour". I disagree. I found this to be sour and not pleasantly so. I cant say I cared for this.

Pours semitransparent reddish brown with a thin brown head that quickly dissipated. Strong fruit taste: cherry in particular of course but plum, figs etc. as well and a bit of alcohol. Fizzy carbonation and rather thin in the mouth. Not a bad beer but not a great one either.
Pretty good Wizen. Aroma of banana and citrus, cloudy amber with long lasting white head, taste is fairly sour, certainly not as sweet as Erdinger which I prefer.

Not usually a fan of IPAs, this was a pleasant surprise. Boulevard calls this their "most heavily hopped beer ever" and the hops are there but they are well balance by a sweet malt and the result is more grapefruit than pine. Very easy to drink and I will be back to this again.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Calling IPA

review_blob: Once upon a time, this was my favorite beer just to keep around to drink and compared to the what we could get not all that long ago, it isnt bad but as my opportunities to try more complex beers has grown so has my recognition that this is very pedestrian. Traditional Hefe Weizen in appearance and aroma with a good long lasting creamy head. Refreshing but not much to it.
Pitch black with a creamy tan head. Lots of chocolate and coffee on the nose. Dark fruit, chocolate and coffee fading to a very nice light burn.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - Dark Truth Stout

review_blob: Very fruity nose. Pitch black with thin head that quickly dissipated. Slightly sweet fades to slightly boozy. Thick/oily on the palate. Had their charcuterie board with this and the beer was wonderful with this. I will be coming back to this one again.
Very smooth, slightly sweet malty taste fading to bitter with just a hint of the alcohol. A very good brew.

This is my first taste of the Westy 12 and as a relative novice at beers generally I will probably edit my ratings after trying a second bottle on another occasion but I will say that, while I dont have enough experience to say whether this is the best beer in the world, it certainly is the best Ive ever had.

Aroma of bananas and yeast, typical cloudy yellow color with a creamy white long lasting head, not too sweet and while the banana notes are clearly present I found the citrus to be more noticeable. Fades to a lightly better taste with a very nice after taste. Im a Weissbier fan and this is one of my favorites.
Pours clear reddish brown with medium lasting creamy tan head. Quite sweet with medium body. I did not find it as complex as I expected.
